18/09/2007
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Serbia will be told where unexploded ordnance may be, left over from the 1999 bombing campaign that ended Serbia's crackdown in Kosovo, NATO headquarters in Brussels confirmed on Monday (September 17th). 
In an interview with Serbian radio B92, the head of the Mine Action Centre in Serbia, Petar Mihajlovic, said he expects the information by October 2nd at the latest. 
Tens of thousands of bombs are strewn across Serbia and have killed ten people over the years. 
(B92 - 18/09/07; Independent, UPI - 17/09/07)
